Introduction

In this part, I analyzed changes to landscape of intra-tumoral macrophages upon p38 blockade by performing differential gene expression analysis and gene set enrichment analysis.

Differential gene expression analysis

Differential gene expression analysis was performed using FindMarkers() from Seurat, with heatmap generated using ComplexHeatmap package.

#perform dge
diff1 <- FindMarkers(mac.seurat, ident.1 = "4T1-Tu-plus-p38i", ident.2 = "4T1-Tu", assay = "originalexp", slot = "data", test.use = "MAST", min.pct = 0.05, logfc.threshold = 0)
dge1 <- diff1[diff1$p_val<0.05, ]

diff2 <- FindMarkers(mac.seurat, ident.1 = "p38a-ko-H9", ident.2 = "4T1-Tu", assay = "originalexp", slot = "data", test.use = "MAST", min.pct = 0.05, logfc.threshold = 0)
dge2 <- diff2[diff2$p_val<0.05, ]

#heatmap markers

genes <- c("Tgfb1", "Vegfa", "Osm", "Ptgs2", "Il1b", "Lpl", "Cd36", "Dusp1", "Ano6", "Sphk1", "Slpi", "Tnfrsf9", "Il7r", "Il1r2", "Rnase2a", "Ccrl2", "Ccr5", "Ccr2", "Ccr1", "Csf1r", "Csf2rb", "Cxcr4", "Cxcl2", "Cxcl1")

mean_mat <- AverageExpression(mac.seurat, group.by = "samplename",
                              layer = "data", features = genes)
mat <- mean_mat[[1]]
mat <- t(scale(t(mat)))
rownames(mat) <- genes
colnames(mat) <- c("Veh", "p38i", "p38ko")
cluster_anno <- unique(mac.seurat$samplename)

quantile(mat, c(0.1, 0.95))
##       10%       95% 
## -1.000107  1.143292
f1 = colorRamp2(c(-1,0,1.2), c("blue","white","red"), space = "RGB")
pngfunc("Plots/QC2/Macrophages/Heatmap_Mac.png", width = 2.3, height  = 5.7)
Heatmap(mat, 
        name="Expression", 
        cluster_rows = FALSE, 
        col = f1, 
        column_split = cluster_anno,
        cluster_columns = FALSE,
        show_column_dend = FALSE,
        cluster_column_slices = TRUE,
        column_title_gp = gpar(fontsize=6),
        row_names_gp = gpar(fontsize=9),
        column_title_rot = 45,
        top_annotation = HeatmapAnnotation(foo=anno_block(gp=gpar(fill=scales::hue_pal()(9)))),
        show_column_names = FALSE,
        use_raster = TRUE,
        raster_quality = 4
)
invisible(dev.off())
include_graphics("Plots/QC2/Macrophages/Heatmap_Mac.png", dpi = 300)

#Violin plots
pngfunc("Plots/QC2/Macrophages/Ptgs2.png", width = 3.5, height = 3)

VlnPlot(mac.seurat, features = "Ptgs2", pt.size = 0, group.by = "samplename", layer = "data") + labs(title = "Ptgs2", x = "", y = "") + theme(axis.text.x = element_blank(), axis.ticks.x = element_blank(), legend.position = "none", plot.title = element_text(face = "italic", hjust = 0.5)) + 
  geom_signif(comparisons = list(c("4T1-Tu-plus-p38i", "4T1-Tu"), c("p38a-ko-H9", "4T1-Tu")), test = "t.test" , test.args = list(alternative = "two.sided", var.equal = FALSE, paired = FALSE), map_signif_level = TRUE, textsize = 7, y_position = c(18, 22), tip_length = 0) + ylim(NA, 25) + scale_fill_manual(values = c("gray71", "deeppink", "forestgreen"))

invisible(dev.off())
include_graphics("Plots/QC2/Macrophages/Ptgs2.png", dpi = 300)

Gene set enrichment analysis (GSEA)

Gene set enrichment analysis was performed using fGSEA and mouse gene ontology (GO): biological processes dataset as reference.

#Loading Mouse Gene Ontology database: Biological processes dataset from MSIGDB-Broad Institute
m_gene_sets <-msigdbr(species = "mouse", category = "C5", subcategory = "GO:BP")
msigdb_list_go_bp <- split(x=m_gene_sets$gene_symbol, f=m_gene_sets$gs_name)

#Creating a numeric vector of log2FC values from the DGE analysis of p38i vs veh 
ranks <- dge1[,2]
names(ranks) <- rownames(dge1)

#Ranking - arranging in decreasing order of logFC values
ranks <- sort(ranks, decreasing = TRUE)

#Running GSEA using fGSEA
fgseares1 <- fgsea(msigdb_list_go_bp, stats=ranks)
fgseares1 <- fgseares1 %>% as_tibble() %>% arrange(desc(NES)) %>% filter(pval<0.05)

df_res1 = data.frame(lapply(fgseares1, as.character), stringsAsFactors=FALSE)

# barplot
pngfunc("Plots/QC2/Macrophages/i_vs_v_mac.png", width = 10, height = 3.5)
ggplot(fgseares1 %>% as_tibble() %>% arrange(desc(NES))
       %>% filter(pval<0.05) %>% head(n=15), 
       aes(reorder(pathway,NES), NES)) +
        geom_col(aes(fill=NES)) +
        coord_flip()+ labs(x="Pathway", y="Normalized Enrichment Score",
                           title="Pathways enriched in p38i") + 
        theme_minimal()
invisible(dev.off())
include_graphics("Plots/QC2/Macrophages/i_vs_v_mac.png", dpi = 300)
